<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
	<title>Tripperist User Guide</title>
	<style>
		:root {
			--primary: #667eea;
			--primary-dark: #764ba2;
			--secondary: #b0b0b0;
			--bg: #1a1a2e;
			--text: #e0e0e0;
			--text-secondary: #b0b0b0;
			--text-tertiary: #7c9fd8;
			--card-bg: #16213e;
			--border: #2a2a3e;
		}

		html.light-mode {
			--bg: #f5f5f5;
			--text: #333;
			--text-secondary: #555;
			--text-tertiary: #667eea;
			--card-bg: #ffffff;
			--border: #e5e5e5;
		}

		body {
			font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
			line-height: 1.6;
			color: var(--text);
			background-color: var(--bg);
			margin: 0;
			padding: 0;
			transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s;
		}

		header {
			background: var(--card-bg);
			border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
			padding: 20px 0;
			position: sticky;
			top: 0;
			z-index: 100;
		}

		.header-container {
			max-width: 900px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 0 20px;
			display: flex;
			justify-content: space-between;
			align-items: center;
		}

		.logo {
			font-size: 1.5em;
			font-weight: bold;
			color: var(--primary);
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		nav {
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 20px;
		}

		nav a {
			text-decoration: none;
			color: var(--text);
			font-weight: 500;
			transition: color 0.3s;
		}

		nav a:hover {
			color: var(--primary);
		}

		.theme-toggle {
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 10px;
			cursor: pointer;
		}

		.toggle-switch {
			width: 50px;
			height: 28px;
			background: var(--border);
			border-radius: 14px;
			position: relative;
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			padding: 0 2px;
			transition: background-color 0.3s;
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
		}

		.toggle-switch.active {
			background: var(--primary);
			border-color: var(--primary);
		}

		.toggle-circle {
			width: 24px;
			height: 24px;
			background: white;
			border-radius: 50%;
			position: absolute;
			left: 2px;
			transition: left 0.3s;
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: center;
			font-size: 14px;
		}

		.toggle-switch.active .toggle-circle {
			left: 24px;
		}

		.toggle-label {
			font-size: 0.9em;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			white-space: nowrap;
		}

		.container {
			max-width: 900px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 40px 20px;
		}

		.page-header {
			text-align: center;
			margin-bottom: 60px;
		}

		h1 {
			color: var(--primary);
			font-size: 2.5rem;
			margin-bottom: 10px;
		}

		.subtitle {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
			color: var(--secondary);
		}

		h2 {
			border-bottom: 2px solid var(--primary);
			padding-bottom: 10px;
			margin-top: 40px;
			color: var(--primary-dark);
		}

		h3 {
			margin-top: 30px;
			color: var(--text);
		}

		.card {
			background: var(--card-bg);
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
			border-radius: 12px;
			padding: 24px;
			margin-bottom: 24px;
			box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
		}

		.feature-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
			gap: 20px;
		}

		table {
			width: 100%;
			border-collapse: collapse;
			margin: 20px 0;
			background: var(--card-bg);
			border-radius: 8px;
			overflow: hidden;
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
		}

		th, td {
			text-align: left;
			padding: 12px 15px;
			border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
			color: var(--text);
		}

		th {
			background-color: var(--primary);
			color: white;
		}

		tr:last-child td {
			border-bottom: none;
		}

		code {
			background: #0f0f1e;
			padding: 2px 6px;
			border-radius: 4px;
			font-family: monospace;
			color: #7c9fd8;
		}

		pre {
			background: #0f0f1e;
			color: #7c9fd8;
			padding: 16px;
			border-radius: 8px;
			overflow-x: auto;
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
		}

		.badge {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: 4px 8px;
			border-radius: 9999px;
			font-size: 0.8rem;
			font-weight: bold;
			background: var(--primary);
			color: white;
			margin-right: 8px;
		}

		.workflow-step {
			display: flex;
			align-items: flex-start;
			margin-bottom: 16px;
		}

		.step-number {
			background: var(--primary);
			color: white;
			width: 28px;
			height: 28px;
			border-radius: 50%;
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: center;
			margin-right: 12px;
			flex-shrink: 0;
			font-weight: bold;
		}

		.phone-mockup {
			border: 8px solid var(--primary);
			border-radius: 24px;
			box-shadow: 0 10px 25px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
			max-width: 100%;
			height: auto;
			margin-bottom: 15px;
			background: var(--border);
		}

		.logo-img {
			max-width: 120px;
			margin-bottom: 20px;
		}

		footer {
			text-align: center;
			margin-top: 60px;
			padding: 40px;
			color: var(--secondary);
			font-size: 0.9rem;
			border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
		}

		footer a {
			color: #7c9fd8;
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		footer a:hover {
			text-decoration: underline;
		}

		ul {
			color: var(--text);
		}

		ul li {
			margin-bottom: 10px;
		}

		strong {
			color: #a8c5e0;
		}

		a {
			color: #7c9fd8;
			text-decoration: none;
			transition: color 0.3s;
		}

		a:hover {
			color: #a8c5e0;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<div class="header-container">
			<a href="index.html" class="logo">Tripperist</a>
			<nav>
				<a href="posts.html">Posts</a>
				<a href="userguide.html">UserGuide</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</header>

	<div class="container">
		<div class="page-header">
			<h1>Tripperist User Guide</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">Your companion for discovering history and points of interest on the road.</p>
		</div>

		<section id="overview" class="card">
			<h2>Product Overview</h2>
			<p>Tripperist is a .NET MAUI application designed for road trippers and local explorers. It leverages the Historical Marker Database (HMDB) and other data sources to provide real-time discovery of your surroundings.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Proximity Discovery:</strong> See what's around you right now.</li>
				<li><strong>Interactive Exploration:</strong> Browse a global map of markers and events.</li>
				<li><strong>Audio-Guided Driving:</strong> Hear about historical sites as you drive past them.</li>
				<li><strong>Trip Planning:</strong> Build custom itineraries for your next adventure.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<h2>Features</h2>
		<div class="feature-grid">
			<div class="card">
				<h3>📍 Nearby Discovery</h3>
				<p>The <strong>Nearby</strong> tab shows a live, distance-sorted list of historical markers within 25 miles.</p>
				<p>Tap any item to open a detail sheet containing descriptions, events, and trip memberships.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<h3>🗺 Explore Map</h3>
				<p>An interactive map that loads markers dynamically as you pan and zoom. Pins cluster together when zoomed out for a cleaner look.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<h3>🚗 Drive Mode</h3>
				<p>Hands-free discovery. The app monitors your GPS and triggers <strong>Text-to-Speech (TTS)</strong> alerts as you approach interesting sites.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<h3>📅 Events</h3>
				<p>A timeline of upcoming festivals, tours, and happenings at historical locations near you.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<section class="card">
			<h2>Upcoming Features</h2>
			<div class="feature-grid">
				<div>
					<h3>🏛 User-Submitted Places <small style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--secondary);">(Phase 12)</small></h3>
					<p>Paste a Google Maps or OSM link — the app auto-fills name, category, and coordinates. Review, edit, and submit for moderation. Track status in <strong>Profile → My Stuff → Saved Places</strong>.</p>
					<p>Import an entire Google Maps saved list at once. Rate limits: <strong>10/day</strong> (Free) &middot; <strong>100/day</strong> (Pro).</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3>🌐 Published Trips &amp; Discover <small style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--secondary);">(Phase 13)</small></h3>
					<p>Share your trips to a global Discover feed. Browse routes curated by other explorers — filter by Near Me, Category, or Recent.</p>
					<p>Preview stops on a map, then <strong>Copy to My Trips</strong> with one tap. Drive Mode works immediately. Attribution preserved: "Based on [title] by [publisher]."</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3>🏆 Achievements &amp; Scavenger Hunts <small style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--secondary);">(Phase 14)</small></h3>
					<p>Check in at historical sites and earn achievement badges. Drive Mode arrival alerts auto-satisfy check-ins. Stats dashboard: visits, states map, streaks, and themed Scavenger Hunts.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3>🛣 Route Corridors <small style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--secondary);">(Phase 15)</small></h3>
					<p>Find all interesting stops along your planned drive, sorted by mile marker. Download the corridor offline for cell-free adventures.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3>🔍 Semantic Search <small style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--secondary);">(Phase 17)</small></h3>
					<p>Find places using natural language: "Civil War markers in a park."</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3>🔄 Real-time Sync <small style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--secondary);">(Phase 20)</small></h3>
					<p>Favorites and Trips sync instantly across all your devices &mdash; no manual refresh needed.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="card">
			<h2>User Interface</h2>
			<h3>Main Navigation</h3>
			<p>Use the bottom Tab Bar to navigate between key areas:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Nearby:</strong> List of the closest points of interest.</li>
				<li><strong>Explore:</strong> Interactive map view.</li>
				<li><strong>Drive:</strong> Specialized map for hands-free driving.</li>
				<li><strong>Events:</strong> Timeline of local happenings.</li>
				<li><strong>Profile:</strong> Your favorites, trips, settings, and &mdash; coming soon &mdash; <strong>My Stuff</strong> for tracking submitted places and published trips.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<h2>Typical Workflows</h2>
		<div class="card">
			<h3>Planning a Trip</h3>
			<div class="workflow-step">
				<div class="step-number">1</div>
				<div>Find a place on the <strong>Explore</strong> map or <strong>Nearby</strong> list.</div>
			</div>
			<div class="workflow-step">
				<div class="step-number">2</div>
				<div>Tap the place to open details, then tap <strong>"Add to Trip"</strong>.</div>
			</div>
			<div class="workflow-step">
				<div class="step-number">3</div>
				<div>Choose an existing trip or select <strong>"＋ New Trip"</strong>.</div>
			</div>

			<h3>Using Drive Mode</h3>
			<div class="workflow-step">
				<div class="step-number">1</div>
				<div>In <strong>Profile > Trips</strong>, select your trip and tap <strong>"Set as Active"</strong>.</div>
			</div>
			<div class="workflow-step">
				<div class="step-number">2</div>
				<div>Navigate to the <strong>Drive</strong> tab and tap <strong>"Start"</strong>.</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<h2>Configuration</h2>
		<p>Customize your experience in <strong>Profile > Settings</strong>.</p>
		<table>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>Setting</th>
					<th>Description</th>
					<th>Default</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><strong>Location Refresh</strong></td>
					<td>How often distances are updated in lists.</td>
					<td>15s</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><strong>Warning Radius</strong></td>
					<td>Distance for the first "Coming up..." alert.</td>
					<td>1.0 mi</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><strong>Arrival Radius</strong></td>
					<td>Distance for the "You have reached..." alert.</td>
					<td>300 ft</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><strong>Alert Cooldown</strong></td>
					<td>Wait time before a place can alert again.</td>
					<td>30 min</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>
		</table>

		<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
		<div class="card">
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Error</th>
						<th>Solution</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>"Unable to determine location"</td>
						<td>Enable Location Services in system settings.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>"No places found nearby"</td>
						<td>Try panning the Explore map or check internet connectivity.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>"Speech Engine Failed"</td>
						<td>Check device Accessibility / Speech settings.</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</div>

		<footer>
			<p>&copy; 2025 Tripperist. Built with .NET MAUI.</p>
		</footer>
	</div>

</body>
</html>
